RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR ATTITUDE coaxed from the gate, chased just off the inside until tipped three wide placed to coaxing at the three-eighths, angled out six wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive issuing a challenge through the final furlong outside the top pair and was just up in the final jumps to the wire. MOVING PICTURES broke open the stall door prior to the start inspired when RAW COURAGE broke through the gate next door, chased five paths off the inside down the backstretch and then three wide through the turn, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled five wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive inside the leader through the final furlong and just missed at the end getting up for the place honors in the last jumps. DADS GOOD RUNNER traded a bump at the start with BAD WATER, showed the way three paths off the inside in hand, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and swung four wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive under growing threat from flanking rivals and was nailed by both in the final strides to the finish. REUNION TOUR four wide in pursuit, got coaxed along from the half mile pole, went eight to nine wide into upper stretch and kicked on belatedly with a mild bid through to the finish. BAD WATER traded a bump at the start with DADS GOOD RUNNER, came under hustling and chased just off the inside, floated briefly three wide directly in front of MOVING PICTURES and was corrected at the three-eighths, went seven wide into upper stretch and weakened. LARZ broke open the stall door just after RAW COURAGE broke through the gate, chased five then four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, went eight wide at the head of the stretch and weakened. RAW COURAGE grew fractious and broke through the gate prior to the start, inspiring LARZ and MOVING PICTURES to open their stall doors in small protest, while the assistant starter kept a firm and strong hold to not allow an escape, got examined and reloaded and chased seven paths off the inside down the backstretch before tucking four wide through the turn, went six wide into upper stretch and was unable to make an impact. THREE-QUARTER FRACTION WAS HAND-TIMED DUE TO A TIMING ISSUE AND PROVIDED BY THE NYRA STEWARD.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISTICAL CURLIN hustled from the gate, showed the way six paths off the inside down the backstretch before tucking to the two path into the turn, came under coaxing nearing the five-sixteenths and began to widen away from the field, cornered just off the inside into upper stretch, forged clear under a drive kept to task until the final strides to the wire. MAJESTIC MICHAEL seven paths off the inside down the backstretch in closest aim of the leader, tucked three wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung four wide into upper stretch, proved no match for the top one while keeping on safe for the place honors. OCASEK coaxed from the start, raced eight paths off the inside down the backstretch and then four to five wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung five wide into upper stretch and stayed on one paced to the finish. EXUDE chased three to four wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, angled five wide into upper stretch and passed tired rivals to the finish. FIRST MONEY coaxed from the gate, chased four paths off the inside down the backstretch and then just off the inside through the turn under a prolonged drive from the half mile pole, continued just off the inside into upper stretch and weakened. RIDE UP began on an awkward first step, raced eight paths off the inside down the backstretch and then five wide through the turn coaxed along from three furlongs out, swung six wide at the top of the stretch and tired.
